# Ignore all
*

# Add metadata and build files
!rollup_bridge_indexer
!pyproject.toml
!*.lock
!README.md

# Add Python code
!**/*.py

# Add configs and scripts (but not env!)
!**/*.graphql
!**/*.json
!**/*.sql
!**/*.yaml
!**/*.yml
!**/*.j2
!**/.keep

# Never copy local-only trees, even though *.py/*.yaml/*.json are re-included above.
# These MUST stay last: .dockerignore is last-match-wins, so a cache's *.json (e.g.
# .mypy_cache/**/*.json) would otherwise be dragged back in by the `!**/*.json` re-include.
# (COPY . ./ now copies from the repo root since the package was flattened.)
.venv/**
.git/**
**/.*_cache
**/.*_cache/**
**/__pycache__
**/__pycache__/**
# Tests never run inside the prod image — the smoke test drives the built image from the
# host via `docker run`, and `package verify` only imports handlers/hooks/types. Keep all
# test code (unit/, e2e/, stand/) out of the shipped image.
tests/**
